The paper deals with decision making for multiple autonomous vehicles, which involves multi-agent systems and robotics (cs.RO) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Nash equilibrium suggests a game theoretic approach (cs.GT), which is often used in multi-agent systems. The focus on safety and velocity suggests a control systems perspective (cs.SY), and the use of numerical simulations suggests a machine learning perspective (cs.LG).
